cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ADRAU-LLM: Appropriate Diagnosis and Rational Antibiotic Use via Large Language Model Fine-Tuning"
message: "If you use this software or model in your research, please cite the following."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: ""  # update with author family names
    given-names: ""   # update with author given names
    orcid: ""         # update with ORCID (optional)
repository-code: "https://github.com/Lysue/ADRAU-LLM"
url: "https://github.com/Lysue/ADRAU-LLM"
abstract: >-
  ADRAU-LLM is a LoRA-fine-tuned, Qwen-based clinical decision support system
  that integrates respiratory infection diagnosis with antimicrobial stewardship.
  Trained on 133,450 real-world outpatient electronic health records and evaluated
  on a temporal hold-out set of 40,559 encounters, the model achieves a Top-1 F1
  score of 0.703 with a 66.2% error reduction compared to the base model.
keywords:
  - clinical decision support
  - large language model
  - respiratory infection
  - antibiotic stewardship
  - LoRA fine-tuning
  - electronic health records
  - antimicrobial resistance
